#: app./scenes/start.py:19
msgid "message.greeting_1"
msgstr ""
"<b>Greetings, {first_name}!</b>\n"
"\n"
"Introducing <b>PocketCDV</b> - a Telegram bot for tracking class schedules at Collegium da Vinci. Our goal is simplicity and accessibility: wherever you are, just two taps and you'll instantly know when your next class is.\n"
"\n"
"Many new features are already in development, and we'll keep you updated on all the latest changes."

#: app./scenes/start.py:23
msgid "button.proceed"
msgstr "Proceed"

#: app./scenes/start.py:36
msgid "message.greeting_2"
msgstr ""
"To get started, we'll need your Wirtualna Uczelnia login credentials. You can enter them by tapping the button below.\n"
"\n"
"A note on privacy: we never store any personal information - your name, email address, or password are never saved. Your schedule is also never stored and is fetched fresh every time you use the bot."

#: app./scenes/start.py:41
msgid "button.login_via_vc"
msgstr "Log in via Wirtualna Uczelnia"
